<h2>Introduction:</h2>
This lab exercises the ability to:
<ul>
    <li>Perform <i>abstraction</i> by defining and calling (using) <i>user-defined functions</i>.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Lab Assignment:</h2>

<ol>
    <li> Create a new directory, <b><tt>Lab8</tt></b>, in your class account directory.</li>
    <li> Move into your Lab8 directory</li>
    <li> Create files <tt>espTest.html</tt>, <tt>magic.html</tt> &amp; <tt>diceRoll.html</tt>.</li>
    <li> For each of the following tasks,
    <ol>
	<li> modify your Web page file via the editor</li>
	<li> save the file</li>
	<li> refresh the browser open to your Web page</li>
	<li> verify that your modifications did what you've intended</li>
    </ol>
    </li>
</ol>
Perform <i>all</i> of the requirements in each of the following Exercises in Reed:
<ol>
    <li> <u>Exercise 9.10</u>
    <li> <u>Exercise 9.12</u>
    <ul>
	<li> You may get your set of responses from <a href="http://8ball.ofb.net/answers.html">here</a>.
    </ul></li>
    <li> <u>Exercise 9.18</u>
    <ul>
	<li> Be sure to display the value of each die before computing the sum.
    </ul></li>
</ol>
    <p>
    When finished (after you’ve proofread your Web page), submit your <b>three</b> sets of files to the appropriate D2L dropbox.
